<h2>Renewal License Requirements</h2>

<a class="bookmark" title="Lead Certification (License) Renewal Eligibility Requirements for Individuals" name="renew-individual"></a>
<h3>Lead Certification (License) Renewal Eligibility Requirements for Individuals</h3>
<p>You are eligible to RENEW your individual lead certification (license) online if you:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Have a lead certification (license) for an individual that is due for renewal.</li>
	<li>Are renewing a license no sooner than 60 days prior to the expiration date and no later than one year or more after the expiration date.</li>
	<li>Completed the appropriate refresher course(s) no sooner than six months prior to the expiration date of the license and no later than one year after the expiration date.</li>
	<li>Are prepared to mail in your complete original and signed renewal application and a copy of the appropriate refresher course(s) completion certificate (you must include a copy of your payment receipt with your application if you paid online).</li>
	<li>Are prepared to pay the appropriate renewal fee and any late renewal fee if renewing after the expiration date (1½ times the normal renewal fee up to 90 days late or 2 times the normal renewal fee from 90 days up to one year late). Please see the <a title="Exam Fees" href="/elp/fees.aspx">exam fees</a> page for a complete schedule of fees.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> <em>A certification that has expired for one year or more may not be renewed. The person may obtain a new license by complying with the requirements and procedures for obtaining an original license.</em></p>

<h4>Important Information About Lead Certifications for Individuals</h4>

<p>If you are an employer, you may pay for your employee's renewal certification through the TexasOnline application, but this certification will not be renewed until all required documents are received and approved. In order to process your certification as soon as possible, you must submit your renewal qualification package immediately following the completion of your online payment.</p>
<p>Practicing with a lapsed certification is prohibited. A person whose certification has been expired for one year or more may not renew the certification. The person may obtain a new certification by complying with the requirements and procedures, including any examination requirements, for obtaining an original (initial) certification. If a certification holder makes a timely and sufficient application for the renewal of a certification, the current certification in his/her possession does not expire until the application has been finally granted or denied by the Licensing Unit.</p>

