<a class="bookmark" title="Lead Training Program Provider Accreditation (License) Renewal Eligibility Requirements" name="renew-training"></a>
<h3>Lead Training Program Provider Accreditation (License) Renewal Eligibility Requirements</h3>
<p>You are eligible to renew your Lead Training Program Provider accreditation (license) online if you:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Have a Lead Training Program Provider Accreditation (license) that is due for renewal.</li>
	<li>Are renewing an accrediation no sooner than 60 days prior to the expiration date and no later than one year or more after the expiration date.</li>
	<li>Are prepared to mail in your complete original and signed renewal application (you must include a copy of your payment receipt with your application if you paid online).</li>
	<li>Are prepared to pay the appropriate renewal fee and any late renewal fees if renewing after the expiration date (1½ times the normal renewal fee up to 90 days late or 2 times the normal renewal fee from 90 days up to one year late. Please see the <a title="Exam Fees" href="/elp/fees.aspx">exam fees</a> page for a complete schedule of fees.</li>
	<li>Can provide a list of courses for which the training program provider is applying for department is applying for department re-accreditation [§295.204(g)(3)(B)]; and</li>
	<li>Can provide a statement signed by the training program manager certifying that the training program provider will at all times comply with all the requirements [§295.204(d)] and [§295.204(f)]; and</li>
	<li>Can provide a statement signed by the training program manager certifying that the training program provider will follow the recordkeeping and reporting requirements in §295.204(j); and</li>
	<li>Can indicate whether there has been any changes or updates to the training facility or equipment since the date of your last accreditation application? If yes, a detailed description of these changes must be provided with the application.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> <em>An accreditation that has expired for one year or more may not be renewed. The Lead Training Program Provider may obtain a new accreditation by complying with the requirements and procedures for obtaining an original (initial) accreditation.</em></p>

